        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 1:10PM CDT by NWS Nashville TN</headline>
        <description>At 110 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nashville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Berry Hill, Forest Hills, Belle Meade, Old Hickory,
Nashville, Whites Creek, Antioch, Oak Hill, Lakewood, Goodlettsville,
and Hendersonville.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between mile markers 202 and 218.
Interstate 65 between mile markers 75 and 95.
Interstate 24 between mile markers 40 and 60.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
Middle Tennessee.</instruction>
